==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bounteous
<hw>Boun"te*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bountevous</ets>, fr. <ets>bounte</ets> bounty.]</ety> <def>Liberal
in charity; disposed to give freely; generously liberal; munificent;
beneficent; free in bestowing gifts; <as>as, <ex>bounteous</ex>
production</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But O, thou <qex>bounteous</qex> Giver of all good.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Boun"te*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Boun"te*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bountied</ent>⟦br⟧
